Program: Discovery
Title: Ocean Blues - noise pollution
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryx4
Last Broadcast Date: 16 February 2005
Is man-made noise in oceans putting marine mammals in peril? The rise in the volume of noise in the world's oceans appears to be affecting the mating and eating habits of both whales and smaller creatures which depend on sound in the darker depths.